   247	
   248	## 5. Defining and Registering New Benchmarks/Datasets
   249	
   250	### Creating a Harbor Adapter (for laude-institute/harbor)
   251	
   252	The [Harbor Adapters documentation](https://harborframework.com/docs/adapters) defines a 9-step process:
   253	
   254	1. **Understand the original benchmark** — Identify task instructions, environments, tests, and solutions
   255	2. **Develop adapter code** — Python code that parses original benchmark format and generates Harbor task directories
   256	3. **Create task directories** — Each task gets `task.toml`, `instruction.md`, `environment/`, `tests/`, `solution/`
   257	4. **Verify oracle solutions** — Run Harbor harness to confirm 100% oracle success rate
   258	5. **Run parity experiments** — Validate adapter output matches original benchmark baseline
   259	6. **Document findings** in `parity_experiment.json`
 succeeded in 51ms:
   130	2. **Installed agents** — Installed directly into the container and executed in headless mode
   131	
   132	Built-in agents include Terminus-2 (Harbor's reference agent), Claude Code, OpenHands, Codex CLI, and MiniSweAgent. Custom agents extend `BaseAgent` from `src/harbor/agents/base.py`.
   133	
   134	### Scaling
   135	
   136	- **Local**: Docker containers, sequential or low concurrency
   137	- **Cloud**: Daytona, Modal, E2B, Runloop, or self-managed GKE Kubernetes clusters — up to thousands of parallel containers via `--env` flag
   138	
   139	### Agent Trajectory Format (ATIF)
   140	
   141	Harbor includes a standardized data format ([ATIF docs](https://harborframework.com/docs/agents/trajectory-format)) that captures complete interaction history, tool calls, LLM metrics (token usage, costs, logprobs), and multi-agent system data — usable for debugging, SFT, and RL pipelines.
   142	
   143	### Benchmark Registry
   144	
   145	Harbor maintains a registry of datasets at [harborframework.com/registry](https://harborframework.com/registry), including Terminal-Bench Pro, SWE-bench Pro, GPQA Diamond, USACO, AlgoTune, BixBench, SWE-Lancer Diamond, and 40+ others.
